      • isEqual

        public static boolean isEqual(Collection one,
                              Collection two)
        Calculates the equality of two collections disregarding the underlying implementation. Specifically this allows (for example) a Collection implemented using an ArrayList and a Collection implemented using a HashSet to be compared for equality.

        This method uses Collection.containsAll(java.util.Collection) to determine equality of the supplied collections.

        Parameters:
        one - a Collection
        two - a Collection
        Returns:
        true if the collections are equal

      • hashCode

        public static int hashCode(Collection c)
        Computes a hash code over c independent of the underlying Collection implementation.

        It is the intent of this method to comply with the Object.hashCode() contract.

        Parameters:
        c - any Collection
        Returns:
        the hash code of the Collection
